#=GF RA Baird NJ, Zhang J, Hamma T, Ferre-D'Amare AR
#=GF RL RNA. 2012;18:759-770.
#=GF RN [10]
#=GF RM 22539525
#=GF RT Structure and folding of a rare, natural kink turn in RNA with an A*A pair
#=GF RT at the 2b*2n position.
#=GF RA Schroeder KT, Daldrop P, McPhee SA, Lilley DM
#=GF RL RNA. 2012;18:1257-1266.
#=GF RN [11]
#=GF RM 23325110
#=GF RT The plasticity of a structural motif in RNA: structural polymorphism of a
#=GF RT kink turn as a function of its environment.
#=GF RA Daldrop P, Lilley DM
#=GF RL RNA. 2013;19:357-364.
#=GF RN [12]
#=GF RM 27016741
#=GF RT A critical base pair in k-turns determines the conformational class
#=GF RT adopted, and correlates with biological function.
#=GF RA Huang L, Wang J, Lilley DM
#=GF RL Nucleic Acids Res. 2016;44:5390-5398.
#=GF RN [13]
#=GF RM 33978763
#=GF RT Structure and folding of four putative kink turns identified in structured
#=GF RT RNA species in a test of structural prediction rules.
#=GF RA Huang L, Liao X, Li M, Wang J, Peng X, Wilson TJ, Lilley DMJ
#=GF RL Nucleic Acids Res 2021;49:5916-5924.
#=GF CC The SAM riboswitch is found upstream of a number of genes which code for
#=GF CC proteins involved in methionine or cysteine biosynthesis in Gram-positive
#=GF CC bacteria. The SAM riboswitch acts at the level of transcription
#=GF CC termination control. The predicted structure consists of a complex
#=GF CC stem-loop region followed by a single stem loop terminator region. An
#=GF CC alternative and mutually exclusive form involves bases in the 3' segment
#=GF CC of helix 1 with those in the 5' region of helix 5 to form a structure
#=GF CC termed the anti-terminator form [1]. This entry represents the conserved
#=GF CC core of the complex structure involving helices 1-4. The structure of SAM
#=GF CC riboswitch has been reported in PDBs: 2GIS, 2YDH, 2YGH, 3GX2, 3GX3, 3GX5,
#=GF CC 3GX6, 3GX7, 3IQN, 3IQP, 3IQR, 3V7E, 4AOB, 4B5R, 4KQY, 5FJC, 5FK1, 5FK2,
#=GF CC 5FK3, 5FK4, 5FK5, 5FK6, 5FKD, 5FKE, 5FKF, 5FKG, 5FKH, 7EAF [5-13]
#=GF WK SAM_riboswitch_(S_box_leader)
#=GF SQ 457

